## If You Are Starting Day 1

If you are reading this at the beginning of your GRC journey — maybe you are on Day 3 or Day 12 and you found this project as a reference — here is the most useful thing I can tell you:

Do the work on a real system. Not a hypothetical system, not a generic healthcare organization, not "System A." Pick a real open-source application (OpenMRS, OSCAR, GNU Health), pick a real cloud environment (AWS free tier, Azure, GCP), pick a real regulatory context (HIPAA, GDPR, SOC 2), and do the work specifically for that system in that environment under those regulations.

The specificity is not just a quality improvement. It is the entire learning mechanism. When you have to answer the question "what is the FIPS 199 confidentiality impact category for THIS system storing THESE records for THESE patients?" you develop the analytical capability that a generic answer cannot produce. When you have to answer "what does the quarterly access review template need to ask for THIS role structure?" you understand access management at a depth that no framework description provides.

The GRC framework is the structure. The specific system is what makes the learning real.

