## What Comes After Day 100

The challenge ends at Day 100. The security program does not. The CP-2 condition still needs Milestones 3 and 4. The AU-12 remediation target date is approaching. The phishing simulation program needs to launch in Q2. The IR-3 tabletop needs to be scheduled. The AUP, Change Management Policy, and Data Retention and Disposal Policy need to move from second-year priorities to active development.

The work continues because security programs are built through ongoing cycles, not completed in a single project. Day 98's most honest observation is that the 97-day capstone is not a finished security program — it is a well-documented first year of a maturing security program. The second year will find gaps the first year did not find. That is not a failure. That is what a functioning monitoring program produces.

The goal was never a perfect score. The goal was an honest, specific, operationally grounded security program for a system that protects vulnerable patients' most sensitive health information. Looking back from Day 98, I believe that is what was built.

